Package: cl-iterate
Version: 1.3.pre1
Revision: 1
Description: Extensible iteration construct
License: BSD
Maintainer: Lars Rosengreen <lars@margay.org>

Type: cl

Depends: clc, clisp-clc | cmucl-clc | openmcl-clc | sbcl-clc

Source: http://common-lisp.net/project/iterate/releases/iterate-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: b027eb449d25951acdbf733491af73bc

SourceDirectory: iterate-%v

PatchScript: head -n 26 iterate.lisp > COPYRIGHT

CompileScript: /usr/bin/true

InstallScript: <<
  find . -type d -exec chmod 755 {} \;
  find . -type f -exec chmod 644 {} \;
  mkdir -p %i/share/common-lisp/source/iterate
  cp -Rp * %i/share/common-lisp/source/iterate
  mkdir -p %i/share/common-lisp/systems
  ln -s %p/share/common-lisp/source/iterate/iterate.asd %i/share/common-lisp/systems/iterate.asd
<<

PostInstScript: %p/sbin/register-common-lisp-source iterate
PreRmScript: %p/sbin/unregister-common-lisp-source iterate

DocFiles: README BUGS ChangeLog doc/iter-man.ps doc/iterate-bare.ps

DescDetail: << 
iterate is an iteration construct for Common Lisp. It is similar to
the CL:LOOP macro, with these distinguishing marks:

  * it is extensible,

  * it helps editors like Emacs indent iterate forms by having a more
    lisp-like syntax, and

  * it isn't part of the ANSI standard for Common Lisp (which is
    sometimes a bad thing and sometimes good).
<<

DescUsage: <<
(asdf:oos 'asdf:load-op 'iterate)
<<

Homepage: http://common-lisp.net/project/iterate/

